<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>Page Not Found | MotherDuck</title>
  <meta name="description" content="The page you're looking for doesn't exist">
</head>
<body>
  <div class="error-container">
    <div class="error-content">
      <div class="duck-icon">ðŸ¦†</div>
      <h1>404</h1>
      <h2>Oops! This duck flew away</h2>
      <p>The page you're looking for doesn't exist or has been moved.</p>
      <div class="error-actions">
        <a href="/" class="home-button">Go Home</a>
        <a href="/docs/about-motherduck/release-notes/" class="docs-button">Browse Docs</a>
      </div>
